</head>
<body class="theme-purple">
    <!----------------->
    <!-- Page Loader -->
    <!----------------->
    @*<div class="page-loader-wrapper">
            <div class="loader">
                <div class="m-t-30"><img src="~/assets/Images/ST-Logo.png" width="48" height="48" alt="Logo"></div>
                <p>Please wait...</p>
            </div>
        </div>*@
    <!------------>
    <!-- Navbar -->
    <!------------>

    <nav class="navbar navbar-fixed-top">
        <div class="container-fluid">
            <div class="navbar-btn">
                <button type="button" class="btn-toggle-offcanvas"><i class="lnr lnr-menu fa fa-bars"></i></button>
            </div>

            <div class="navbar-brand">
                <a img src="~/assets/Images/ST-Logo.png" alt="Status Tracker Logo" style="width: 48px; height:48px" class="img-responsive logo"></a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </nav>

    <div class="text-center" style="margin-top: 180px">
        <h1 class="display-1 text-warning">Welcome</h1>
    </div>

    <style>
        body {
            background-image: url('/assets/Images/auth_bg.jpg');
            background-repeat: no-repeat;
            background-size: cover;
        }
    </style>

    <!------------------>
    <!-- Login Button -->
    <!------------------>
    <a class="nav-link btn btn-warning" asp-area="Identity" asp-page="/Account/Login" style="position:fixed; top:50%; left:55%; margin-right:-45%; transform: translate(-50%, -50%)">
        Login
    </a>

    <!--------------------------------------------------->
    <!-- Button to Open the Modal on the Landing page.-->
    <!--------------------------------------------------->
    <button type="button" style="position:fixed; top:50%; left:50%; margin-right:-50%; transform: translate(-50%, -50%)" class="btn btn-warning" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#myModal">
        About
    </button>

    <!--------------->
    <!-- The Modal -->
    <!---------------> 
    <div class="modal" id="myModal">
        <div class="modal-dialog-centered modal-dialog modal-xl">
            <div class="modal-content">
                <!-- Modal Header -->
                <div class="modal-header justify-content-center">
                    <h4 class="modal-title text-warning">~ Status Tracker ~</h4>
                </div>
                <!-- Modal body -->
                <div class="modal-body bg-dark">
                    <pre class="text-warning" style="font-size:medium">
             Status Tracker is a Web-based software application designed to track and manage trouble tickets.
             If a company develops products or services, whether for in-house use or distribution, a "bug" 
             tracking system can keep an accurate record of the development process for each project basis.
             
             Status Tracker is built as a Web-based service application using the Microsoft Visual Studio 2019,
             MVC architecture, MS Code-First database schema using Entity Framework with user and role-level 
             security, and web pages built with HTML4, Twitter Bootstrap, and model binding with Razor.
             
             Status Tracker is a commercial-grade application that meets professional standards, allows users to
             tract tickets from origination to close. Sort, filter, or search, by priority, status or type, 
             and manage users, and assign tasks.
             
             Status Tracker is fully secured using Authentication and Authorization through Microsoft Entity 
             Framework to prevent unauthorized persons from accessing user profile and account information.
                    </pre>
                </div>
                <!-- Modal footer -->
                <div class="modal-footer">
                    <button type="button" class="btn btn-outline-warning" data-dismiss="modal">Close</button>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>   

    <footer class="border-top footer w-100 fixed-bottom text-center">
        <div class="container text-warning">
            &copy; 2020 ~ Status Tracker ~ Created by: O J OLMO - Full Stack Developer
        </div>
    </footer>
    <script src="~/js/libscripts.bundle.js"></script>
    
</body>
</html>